tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE bioreactor_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  design_name VARCHAR(100),
  date_started DATE,
  temperature FLOAT,
  pressure FLOAT,
  efficiency FLOAT,
  effectiveness FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE BioreactorDesigns (
    bioreactor_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    design_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    dimensions VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    efficiency_score FLOAT,
    effectiveness_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE OperationalData (
    data_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT REFERENCES BioreactorDesigns(bioreactor_id),
    operation_date DATE NOT NULL,
    temperature FLOAT,
    pH FLOAT,
    pressure FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE bioreactor_designs (
    bioreactor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    design_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    manufacturer VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    height FLOAT NOT NULL,
    width FLOAT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE operational_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT NOT NULL,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    parameter_value FLOAT NOT NULL,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE efficiency_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT NOT NULL,
    efficiency_score FLOAT NOT NULL,
    effectiveness_score FLOAT NOT NULL,
    recorded_date DATE NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE bioreactor_designs (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    design_name VARCHAR(100),
    dimensions VARCHAR(50),
    material VARCHAR(50),
    capacity_liters DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE operational_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT,
    operation_date DATE,
    temperature_celsius DECIMAL(5,2),
    ph_level DECIMAL(3,2),
    agitation_speed RPM
);

CREATE TABLE efficiency_data (
    efficiency_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT,
    data_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    yield_kg DECIMAL(8,2),
    energy_consumption_kwh DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE effectiveness_data (
    effectiveness_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT,
    data_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    efficiency_rating DECIMAL(5,2),
    maintenance_status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE operational_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bioreactor_id INT,
    date DATE,
    temperature DECIMAL,
    pressure DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE operators (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    operator_name VARCHAR(50),
    bioreactor_id INT,
    shift_start DATETIME,
    shift_end DATETIME
);
